    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "V420l",
      "x": -471,
      "y": 3870,
      "name": "Dashboard-Plan-Comment-final",
      "width": 1440,
      "height": 340,
      "content": "<!--\n## Dashboard Design Plan\n\n**Type:** plan\n**Component:** Dashboard (entire pass)\n**Source of truth:** dashboard-build-plan.md lines 121–239\n\n### Scope (from build plan)\n- /login — two OAuth buttons (GitHub, Google)\n- / — single unified dashboard. All connected repos in one scrollable list.\n- /connect — connect-a-repo flow\n- /[workspace]/[repo]/[branch] — existing AppShell with new breadcrumb dropdown at top of sidebar\n\n### Visual rules (locked)\n- Pragmatic, dense, type-driven, monochrome. References: Linear, Vercel deployments, Cron.\n- Rows 48–64px tall, single line, monospace where data is technical (org/repo, SHA, timestamps).\n- Status indicators are small dots/chips, never colored backgrounds.\n- No card grids, no tiles, no recently-opened carousels.\n- Hover reveals secondary actions; default state is calm.\n- Repos identify by org/repo text, no per-project emoji avatars.\n\n### Component set built in this pass\n1. AuthButton (GitHub / Google variants — default, hover)\n2. TopBar (search, +Connect new repo, user)\n3. RepoRow (default, hover, expanded, syncing, failed, stale)\n4. WorkspaceChip (personal, team — default, hover)\n5. WorkspacePopover (member list with Manage members)\n6. BranchRow (default, hover, syncing, failed, stale; pinned/unpinned)\n7. StatusDot + StatusChip (synced, syncing, failed, stale)\n8. OtherBranchesExpander (collapsed, expanded, loading)\n9. EmptyState (no repos)\n10. ConnectRepoForm (idle, GitHub installations list, workspace assignment)\n11. InstanceBreadcrumb (default, branch dropdown open) for AppShell\n\n### Dashboard layout mockups (1440px, all built in this pass)\n- LoginScreen-default-final\n- Dashboard-empty-final (no repos connected)\n- Dashboard-populated-final (collapsed repo rows)\n- Dashboard-expanded-final (one repo expanded with branches + popover)\n- ConnectRepo-default-final\n- AppShell-with-breadcrumb-final (existing shell + new breadcrumb)\n\n### Tokens (locked from existing canvas)\n- Text primary #121111 / secondary #6d6467 / muted #9b9295\n- Borders #dfe0e7 / dividers #e6e7ef / hover bg #f6f6f9 / surface bg #eff0f5 / panel bg #ffffff\n- Radius 8 (controls), 14 (pills/triggers), 16 (panels)\n- Type Geist 10/12/13/14, weights normal/500\n- Mono Geist Mono / IBM Plex Mono fallback for org/repo, SHA, timestamps\n-->"
    },
    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "sZN5H",
      "x": -471,
      "y": 5400,
      "name": "Dashboard-Components-Kit-Container",
      "width": 3590,
      "fill": "#eff0f5ff",
      "cornerRadius": 24,
      "layout": "vertical",
      "gap": 48,
      "padding": 48,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "vaZGA",
          "name": "KitTitle",
          "fill": "#121111",
          "content": "Dashboard Component Kit",
          "lineHeight": 1.2,
          "fontFamily": "Geist",
          "fontSize": 24,
          "fontWeight": "500"
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "R90VqO",
          "name": "Section-AuthButton",
          "context": "<!--\n## Section-AuthButton\n\n**Type:** component\n**Component:** AuthButton\n\n### Purpose\nWraps every AuthButton variant for the /login screen.\n\n### Design notes\n- 44 tall pill, radius 14, padding [0,20], gap 10.\n- GitHub uses #121111 fill / white text + lucide `github` icon.\n- Google uses #ffffff fill / #121111 text + lucide `globe` icon (chrome icon does NOT exist in lucide).\n- Hover lifts via subtle outer shadow.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Demonstrates the four states wired to the GitHub-or-Google flow.\n- Sibling sections live in `sZN5H`.\n- Preserve fill/stroke semantics — never invert GitHub/Google color identity.\n-->",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "#ffffff",
          "cornerRadius": 16,
          "stroke": {
            "align": "inside",
            "thickness": 1,
            "fill": "#dfe0e7"
          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 16,
          "padding": 24,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Fzzc9",
              "name": "AuthButton-Heading",
              "fill": "#121111",
              "content": "AuthButton",
              "lineHeight": 1.2,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "BuuNR",
              "name": "AuthButton-Desc",
              "fill": "#6d6467",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Login-screen primary action. GitHub is the canonical path, Google joins by invite.",
              "lineHeight": 1.4,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "yzpvm",
              "name": "AuthButton-Display",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "fill": "#f6f6f9",
              "cornerRadius": 12,
              "gap": 32,
              "padding": 24,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "hjo5R",
                  "name": "AuthButton-GitHub-Default-Group",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 8,
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "LprP4",
                      "fill": "#9b9295",
                      "content": "Default",
                      "lineHeight": 1,
                      "fontFamily": "Geist",
                      "fontSize": 10,
                      "fontWeight": "500"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "tGNOc",
                      "name": "AuthButton-GitHub-default-final",
                      "context": "<!--\n## AuthButton-GitHub-default-final\n\n**Type:** variant\n**Variant:** default\n**Component:** AuthButton (GitHub)\n\n### Purpose\nPrimary GitHub sign-in CTA at rest.\n\n### Design notes\n- Fill #121111, text/icon #ffffff, radius 14, height 44, padding [0,20], gap 10.\n- Icon `github` (lucide) 16x16.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Sibling hover variant lives in this section.\n- Never substitute the icon — `chrome` does not exist in lucide.\n-->",
                      "height": 44,
                      "fill": "#121111",
                      "cornerRadius": 14,
                      "gap": 10,
                      "padding": [
                        0,
                        20
                      ],
                      "justifyContent": "center",
