        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "qQaV5",
          "name": "Dashboard-populated-v2-wrap",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 12,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Pqzak",
              "name": "v2Label",
              "fill": "#9b9295",
              "content": "03b / Dashboard — populated v2 (with featured cards section)",
              "lineHeight": 1,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 12,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "vyo5t",
              "name": "Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final",
              "context": "<!--\n## Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** populated + featured-cards iteration\n**Component:** Dashboard\n\n### Purpose\nExploratory iteration of the populated dashboard with a 'Recently active' card section above the canonical 'All repos' list. Intended to evaluate a hero-card affordance for high-frequency repos without abandoning the dense list pattern below.\n\n### Tension with build plan\nBuild-plan line 153 explicitly says 'No card-based grids, no big tiles, no recently-opened carousels.' This layout deliberately departs from that rule per user direction to explore highlight cards. Treat this as an A/B candidate, not the canonical surface — `Dashboard-populated-final` (sibling) remains the no-cards reference.\n\n### Design notes\n- Section heading 'Recently active' (Geist 16/500) + Geist 12 #9b9295 muted meta (`Last 7 days`).\n- Cards: white surface, radius 16, 1px #dfe0e7, no heavy preview imagery (per user direction). Card density mirrors Reference17 cards (Reference16/17 are pinned on the canvas as moodboard).\n- Each card carries: org/repo (Geist Mono 14), branch + last-sync meta, StatusChip top-right, component-count footer meta, primary 'Open' pill action footer-right.\n- Below cards: existing 'All repos' page header + RepoList (copied verbatim from `Dashboard-populated-final` so this iteration matches the canonical content).\n\n### For AI agents\n- Card variants explored further in `FeaturedRepoCard-iterations-final` (sibling block in `pzqsk`): Iteration A (this layout), Iteration B (compact), Iteration C (metrics-led), Iteration D (activity-led).\n- Treat the all-repos list panel as the source of truth for repo data; the cards are derived selections (most active, most recently synced, etc.).\n- Do not delete `Dashboard-populated-final`. The two coexist deliberately until the user picks one.\n-->",
              "clip": true,
              "width": 1440,
              "height": 1280,
              "fill": "#f6f6f9ff",
              "cornerRadius": 16,
              "stroke": {
                "align": "inside",
                "thickness": 1,
                "fill": "#dfe0e7"
              },
              "layout": "vertical",
              "children": [
                {
                  "id": "Co9pM",
                  "type": "ref",
                  "ref": "KJinn",
                  "name": "v2Tb"
                },
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "a6yae",
                  "name": "v2-Main",
                  "context": "<!-- ## v2-Main\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** populated v2 main\n**Component:** Dashboard-populated-v2 main column\n### Design notes\n- Order top→bottom: FeaturedRepos-Section (cards) → v2-Page-Header (All repos) → v2-RepoList. Padding [32,80] matches Dashboard-populated-final.\n-->",
                  "width": "fill_container",
